Magit is front end, or "porcelain" for the [[Git]] version control system.

* Homepage: http://magit.github.io
* Manual: http://magit.github.io/documentation
* Issues: http://github.com/magit/magit/issues

== Crash Course ==

Getting started with Magit is really easy:
 
* ##M-x magit-status## to see git status, and in the status buffer:
* ##s## to stage files
* ##c c## to commit (type the message then ##C-c C-c## to actually commit)
* ##b b## to switch to another branch

Other handy keys:

* ##P P## to do a git push
* ##F F## to do a git pull
* try to press ##TAB##

== Extensions ==

Various packages exist which extend Magit.

* [https://github.com/magit/magit-annex magit-annex] use ##git annex## within Magit
* [https://github.com/magit/magit-filenotify magit-filenotify] refresh status buffer when git tree changes
* [https://github.com/terranpro/magit-gerrit magit-gerrit] Magit plugin for Gerrit Code Review
* [https://github.com/sigma/magit-gh-pulls magit-gh-pulls] Magit plugin for dealing with GitHub pull requests
* [https://github.com/jtatarik/magit-gitflow magit-gitflow] ## git flow## extension for Magit
* [https://github.com/tarsius/magit-push-remote magit-push-remote] Push remote support for Magit
* [https://github.com/magit/magit-tramp magit-tramp] Git method for Emacs Tramp
* [https://github.com/magit/orgit orgit] support for Org links to Magit buffers
* [https://github.com/magit/org-magit org-magit] link to magit from org documents

